## DATA FLOW WITH YOUR CONFIG

```
1. DOCTOR CREATES REFERRAL
   ↓
   ReferralsController (Port 5001)
   ├─ Read config: ExternalServices.PhysiotherapyApi.BaseUrl
   ├─ Get patient's ExternalPatientId (from DB or Redis cache)
   ├─ Create referral in DB
   ├─ Publish event to MessageBroker.ConnectionString
   └─ Response: "Pending_ExtSync"

2. RABBITMQ HOLDS MESSAGE
   ↓
   RabbitMQ (amqp://localhost:5672)
   ├─ Exchange: clinic.orthopedic.events
   ├─ Queue: clinic.referral.created
   └─ Persists message (survives server restart)

3. PHYSIOTHERAPY CONSUMES
   ↓
   FastAPI (http://localhost:8000)
   ├─ Connects to RabbitMQ
   ├─ Gets referral message
   ├─ Creates referral in PostgreSQL
   ├─ Publishes "ReferralAccepted"
   └─ Message goes to clinic.referral.accepted queue

4. ORTHOPEDIC RECEIVES CALLBACK
   ↓
   Orthopedic System (Port 5001)
   ├─ Receives ReferralAccepted from RabbitMQ
   ├─ Updates referral status: "Accepted_Ext"
   ├─ Caches result in Redis (ExternalPatientCache)
   ├─ If retry needed: Uses Resilience.Retry config
   └─ Response: "Accepted by Physiotherapy" ✓

5. DOCTOR SEES UPDATE
   ↓
   Frontend
   ├─ Polls IntegrationStatusController
   ├─ Gets latest status from cache (Redis)
   ├─ Shows "Referral accepted by Physiotherapy"
   └─ Displays Physio's appointment schedule
```

