## HOW YOUR CONFIG ENABLES FAILURE RECOVERY

### Scenario 1: Physiotherapy is Down
```
Doctor creates referral → Message sent to RabbitMQ
↓
RabbitMQ stores safely (not lost)
↓
Doctor sees: "Pending - waiting for response"
↓
[Physiotherapy comes back online]
↓
RabbitMQ auto-delivers queued messages
↓
Doctor sees: "Accepted by Physiotherapy" ✓
```

### Scenario 2: Network Timeout
```
Orthopedic calls Physiotherapy API
↓
Resilience.Retry.MaxAttempts = 4
↓
Retry 1: Wait 100ms (InitialDelayMs)
Retry 2: Wait 200ms (100ms * BackoffMultiplier)
Retry 3: Wait 400ms
Retry 4: Wait 800ms
↓
If still failing: Move to DeadLetterQueue
↓
Operations team alerts + manual review
```

### Scenario 3: Physiotherapy API Overloaded
```
50% of requests failing (Resilience.CircuitBreaker.FailureThreshold)
↓
Circuit Breaker = OPEN
↓
Stop sending requests for 30 seconds
↓
After 30 sec: Try 1 test request (HALF-OPEN state)
↓
If success: Circuit = CLOSED (resume normal)
If fails: OPEN again (wait another 30 sec)
```

